ealistic mock images of nearby galaxies. The new curved\nsize-luminosity relations will prevent over or under estimates of bulge, disk\nand galaxy sizes at all magnitudes. These results complement the analysis of\nQuilley & de Lapparent (2022) by providing the joint size and luminosity\nvariations of bulges and disks, as they evolve reversely along the Hubble\nsequence.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 May 2023 12:17:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-04"}
